OL,3,CWhy parents are calling for an under-
OL,4,C16s social media ban
OL,6,FSapna said: "There is a body of
OL,7,Fevidence demonstrating the harms that
OL,8,Fsocial media is causing to our
OL,9,Fchildren, we're coming together to ask
OL,10,Fthe government to raise the age of
OL,11,Fsocial media to 16 to allow our
OL,12,Fchildren to have those years where
OL,13,Fthey can just be children, and develop
OL,14,Fin a healthy way."
OL,16,FThe proposed ban is an amendment to
OL,17,Fthe Children's Wellbeing and Schools
OL,18,FBill that would require social media
OL,19,Fcompanies to stop children under 16
OL,20,Fusing their platforms.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/16
